20Z", "updated_at": "2016-05-02T14:58:28Z", "closed_at": "2016-05-02T14:58:28Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Given that `std::os::args()` returns a `Vec<String>`, and `String`s and `&str` aren't directly comparable, I think the following pattern will be pretty common:\n1. Rust newbie tries to implement a simple program (possibly her/his first) that pattern matches on a command line argument:\n   \n   ``` rust\n   match std::os::args()[0] {\n       \"something\" => { /* ... */ },\n       _ => { /* ... */ },\n   }\n   ```\n2. Rust newbie gets a scary error message that talks about structs and pointers:\n   \n   ```\n   mismatched types: expected `collections::string::String` but found `&'static str` (expected struct collections::string::String but found &-ptr)\n   ```\n3. Rust newbie gets frustrated\n\nIs it possible to create a friendlier error message if someone tries to compare a `&str` and a `String`, possibly with a link to [the string guide](http://doc.rust-lang.org/guide-strings.html)?\n", "closed_by": {"login": "arielb1", "id": 1830974, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4MzA5NzQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1830974?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1", "html_url": "https://github.com/arielb1", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/arielb1/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "